remarks: Harpalus sp. 90 degree anterior angle that fans out over the elytra. Probably either HAROPA or HARELL.
Harpalus sp. single setae above eye. Base of pronotum rather flat. Punctuation around pronotum fovea. Body rufo-testaceous
Cymindis sp. similar in look but smaller than Morph M. Head pronotum and legs rufous. Elytra rufo-testaceous.
Amara sp. might be Morph J. similar fovea and punctuation. Pronotum very flat at base. Darker in color.
Harpalus sp. 90 degree anterior angle that fans out over the elytra. Probably either HAROPA or HARELL.
Cymindis sp. Legs and antenna rufous in color. Body piceous. Latter margins of pronotum translucent. Punctuation all over head and pronotum and down stria.
Helluomorphoides sp. Heavily punctated all over. Rufous in color. Long slender elytra with squarish apex.
slightly larger than AMACON3. Only segments 1 and 2 of antenna rufous. Two slight fovea on pronotum. Pronotum relatively smooth.
